(1)División Cirugía, Instituto Nacional de Cancerología, México, D.F., México.

OBJECTIVE: To evaluate prognostic factor differences between surviving and 
decreased breast cancer patients in clinical stage IV with supraclavicular or 
contralateral axilla metastasis when first seen.
METHODS: From the clinical records of 13 years (1975-88) two groups of ten 
patients each were obtained. Group 1 were women alive and free of disease for 
